sc_cat_item.description:
This catalog item allows you to deploy firewall rules provided via a Ports and Protocol Form in the csv format. This deployment is automated, and ends up in the global firewall governing IBMs FDC Virtual Network layer. The length of deployment is a variable that is contingent on the number of rules being deployed, and depending on how many new services/IP-scopes that need to be created in tangent with the deployment. However, generally, deployments on average take ten minutes.

Please ensure the ppf provided is in csv format, and has headers in accordance with this structure:

Description:, Protocol:, Source Hostname:, Source Address/Network:, Destination Hostname:, Destination Address/Network:, Destination Port:

IP/Services fields that are left blank will be considered, 'ANY' where applicable. It is important the headers follow this structure as it streamlines parsing of the attachment. Any PPF not in accordance with this format will be considered malformed, and no rules will be deployed. The workflow will end, and a task will be created, and linked to the parent Request Item with the description of the exact error.

Upon submission this item will proceed through approval from the appropriate parties. Once approved the actual deployment will begin. Please Reference Application Manual On The Acceptable Values For Fields In An Automated PPF.

**This Application is still in development. As such some error checking takes place in regards to the input, however, not everything will be caught (e.g. Mis-typed values in a correctly formed ppf wont be caught until NSX rejects them) Engineer Intuition is still strongly advised
